com.pega.pegarules.pub.session

Class PassivationKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pega.pegarules.pub.session.PassivationKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class PassivationKey
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A four part key used both to uniquely identify PassivationRecords and to query for records with certain key values. Implementers of CustomPassivationMechanism are free to serialize instances of this class, but must pay careful attention to the serialVersionUID if using Java Serialization. Two keys are considered to be equal when all of their fields are equal. A less strict equality operation is defined in the matches(PassivationKey) method.

      • matches

        public boolean matches(PassivationKey aPartialKey)
        Returns true if this key matches the provided partial key. A partial key is a PassivationKey object that has unspecified values for some or all of its fields. This method determines matching by applying the following algorithm:
        • If aPartialKey.getType() != ANY, it's type must exactly match this key's type.
        • If aPartialKey.getRequestor() != null, it's requestor id must exactly match this key's requestor id.
        • If aPartialKey.getThreadName() != null, it's thread name must exactly match this key's thread name.
        • If aPartialKey.getPageName() != null, it's page name must exactly match this key's page name.

        For example, if this is a key for a thread with a requestor ID of H7F8AF0BFDCFD32398D34D13C94E9010A and a name of MyWorkThread, this method would return true for:

        • aPartialKey with type THREAD and null requestor ID, thread name, and page name
        • aPartialKey with type THREAD and requestor ID of H7F8AF0BFDCFD32398D34D13C94E9010A, a null thread name, and a null page name
        • aPartialKey with type THREAD and requestor ID of H7F8AF0BFDCFD32398D34D13C94E9010A, a thread name of MyWorkThread, and a null page name
        • aPartialKey with type ANY and null requestor ID, thread name, and page name
        • aPartialKey with type ANY and requestor ID of H7F8AF0BFDCFD32398D34D13C94E9010A, a null thread name, and a null page name
        • aPartialKey with type ANY and requestor ID of H7F8AF0BFDCFD32398D34D13C94E9010A, a thread name of MyWorkThread, and a null page name

        Note that due to the fact that the values of aPartialKey dictate which comparisons are performed, this method is not commutative.

        Parameters:
        aPartialKey -
        Returns:
        True if this key matches aPartialKey, false otherwise.
